🔥 1. DRIVER (Brain of the job)

👉 This is where your .py file runs
Responsibilities:
Creates SparkSession
Builds execution plan (DAG)
Sends tasks to executors

Example:

spark = SparkSession.builder.appName("Test").getOrCreate()
👉 Driver only plans, doesn’t process big data

⚙️ 2. CLUSTER MANAGER (Resource Allocator)

Examples:

Standalone
YARN
Kubernetes

👉 It decides:

How many executors
How much memory
Where to run them

💪 3. EXECUTORS (Workers)

👉 Actual work happens here

Each executor:

Runs on a node
Executes tasks
Stores data in memory

📦 4. TASKS (Smallest Unit)
A job is split into stages
Each stage into tasks

👉 Each task processes one partition of data

📊 5. DAG (Directed Acyclic Graph)

This is the real brain logic

When you write:

df.filter(...).groupBy(...).count()

Spark builds a DAG of transformations

👉 Nothing runs yet (lazy execution)

⚡ 6. LAZY EVALUATION (Most asked interview concept)

Transformations:

filter
select
groupBy

👉 Don’t execute immediately

Action:

show()
count()
collect()

👉 Triggers execution

🔄 7. SHUFFLE (Where performance dies)

Happens during:

groupBy
join
reduceByKey

👉 Data moves across network → expensive

⚠️ This is where optimization questions come from

🔥 END-TO-END FLOW (Understand this clearly)
You write PySpark code
Driver creates DAG
DAG split into stages
Tasks sent to executors
Executors process partitions
Results returned
